== Welcome to The Real Fantasy Football

- Dependencies

1. Ruby 1.9.3 
	Download here: http://ftp.ruby-lang.org/pub/ruby/1.9/ruby-1.9.3-p194.tar.gz
	OR
	sudo port install ruby19
	
2. RubyGems
	Download here: http://rubyforge.org/frs/?group_id=126
	OR
	sudo port install rb-rubygems
	
3. Bundler
	sudo gem install bundler
	

- Initial setup

1. Clone this project
	git clone git@github.com:SomeRandomGuys/fantasy_football_rails_app.git

2. Run bundler from root of the project
	bundle install
	
3. Create database (Assuming postgres is correctly setup and is using default settings)
	rake db:schema:load

4. Load seed data (League, Teams, Players etc.)
	rake db:seed
	
4. Run development server from a terminal
	rails server
	
5. Now you should have a running rails instance (APIs and the web app)
	http://localhost:3000/apidoc
	
	
- Moar Information

* The Getting Started Guide: http://guides.rubyonrails.org/getting_started.html
* Ruby on Rails Tutorial Book: http://www.railstutorial.org/